The paper deals with multi-class learning and generalization error bounds, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses empirical risk minimization algorithms and linear function classes, which are relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper applies its results to multi-class support vector machines, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses empirical $\ell_\infty$-norm covering numbers, which are relevant to the field of statistics (cs.ST).
